Various neuron-specific antisera have been used to counterstain the cells containing ependymin-like immunoreactivity .
Fluoro-Gold was injected intraperitoneally to counterstain cardiac ganglionic principal neurons ( PNs ) .
Propidium iodide was used to counterstain nuclei .
Eosinol counterstain for routine paraffin embedded tissue .
Acridine - orange DNA microfluorimetry with Giemsa counterstain .
